Texture Takeaways:

✅ Low & Slow - it’s easy to “Break” a Curl Pattern so use low volumes of peroxide, gentle lightener types, & bond builders 

Example: @oligopro Lightening Cream (the *Best* Oil Based Lightener) & @olaplex

✅ Chunky Pick-Ups - skinny highlights disappear when Curl Expands so try Zigzag Teasie-Lights 

Technique Combo: 

#GeodesicFoilayage + 
#HairlineShuffle + 
#LockStitchFoilayage

✅ Carve and Slice - cut across the hair at angle 📐 (never shave on top of the cuticle with a blade parallel to the hair) and slice internal weight to avoid the “Pyramid Look” 

* Also, disconnected Layers creates shorter pieces underneath that internally push up long layers for Crown Volume without too short of layers at the Top 🔝

✅ Treatment 🎁 @k18hair 💪

💦 Gloss Formula:

@oligopro Calura Gloss 
Roots 7N & 7AI 
Mids-Ends 9GV & 10NB

www.ashleenormanhair.com

Tool ⚒️ @ashleenormanhair 6.75 Shears ✂️

Client: “I need a Haircut BUT - I Don’t want to lose any length, I Don’t want Bangs, All the Layers need to go back into a Ponytail, I Want to be able to part it anywhere, and I Want Movement & Shape” 

Hairstylist: 🤔🤨😳....💡🤯🤓

1. “M” Frame - “V” + Side Bits = A center point of weight that can swing to either side part or even from the middle with connected side layers

2. “V” Layer in Top Horseshoe (Cutting on the “Bias”) - crisscrossing diagonal sections to once again create a center point of weight that can swing like a pendulum 

3. Connect sides to Faceframe for Round length line 

4. Concave Layers Undercut below Top Horseshoe - Internal weight removal 

*Disconnected Layers swing separately from each other to maximize movement in the back without creating short layers at the top crown 👸

Step 3: Pre-Dry focusing on the Root Direction - flat wrap the roots opposite to natural fall to create Volume using the @dysonhairpro Super Sonic Pro

Step 4: Section in 3 large Cirlces - starting in the Hairline front to back

Step 5: Flat Brush “C” Shapes into the Hair by over-directing the hair forward and then back using a @behairfulbrush 

Notes 📝 

* direct the nozzle of the blow dryer down the cuticle layer not straight at the hair using the face of the boar hair brush to smooth and create shine ✨ 

* Never touch the nozzle to the brush - if the natural boar hair bristles of the brush become burnt 🥵 then what do you think is happening to the clients hair? 

Step 6: Spray ANH “Roll in the Hay” Texture Spray thoroughly section by section directed at the roots to soak up oils and add volume 

Step 7: Scrunch in ANH “Oh Behave Cream” at the Mids-ends to add separations and definition

Texture Takeaways:

✅ Low & Slow - it’s easy to “Break” a Curl Pattern so use low volumes of peroxide, gentle lightener types, & bond builders 

Example: @oligopro Lightening Cream (the *Best* Oil Based Lightener) & @olaplex

✅ Chunky Pick-Ups - skinny highlights disappear when Curl Expands so try Zigzag Teasie-Lights 

Technique Combo: 

#GeodesicFoilayage + 
#HairlineShuffle + 
#LockStitchFoilayage

✅ Carve and Slice - cut across the hair at angle 📐 (never shave on top of the cuticle with a blade parallel to the hair) and slice internal weight to avoid the “Pyramid Look” 

* Also, disconnected Layers creates shorter pieces underneath that internally push up long layers for Crown Volume without too short of layers at the Top 🔝

Featuring @ashleenormanhair Styling Products 🙌

* available on website- link in profile 
* available to Licensed Hairstylist for Retail- DM for the Wholesale Link 😘🙏💕

Step 1: Spray ANH “Thick and Fresh” thoroughly section by section root to ends in clean towel dried hair 

Step 2: Section the Front from the back from where the Top of Head rounds forward to the front of the Ears 

Step 3: Pre-Dry focusing on the Root Direction - flat wrap the roots opposite to natural fall to create Volume using the @dysonhairpro Super Sonic Pro

Step 4: Section in 3 large Cirlces - starting in the Hairline front to back

Step 5: Flat Brush “C” Shapes into the Hair by over-directing the hair forward and then back using a @behairfulbrush 

Notes 📝 

* direct the nozzle of the blow dryer down the cuticle layer not straight at the hair using the face of the boar hair brush to smooth and create shine ✨ 

* Never touch the nozzle to the brush - if the natural boar hair bristles of the brush become burnt 🥵 then what do you think is happening to the clients hair? 

Step 6: Spray ANH “Roll in the Hay” Texture Spray thoroughly section by section directed at the roots to soak up oils and add volume 

Step 7: Scrunch in ANH “Oh Behave Cream” at the Mids-ends to add separations and definition
